lt in unintended meanings depending on word choice, a particular phrase, or even one’s inflection. A recent study of corporate managers found that one out of five projects fail primarily because of ineffective transnational communication, resulting in the loss of millions of dollars. In Words Matter, you will venture into the halls of multinational tech companies around the world to study language and culture at work; learn practical steps for harnessing research in communication and anthropology to become more skilled in the digital workplace; and learn to use the “Communication Plus Model,” which can be easily applied in multiple situations, leading to better communication and better business outcomes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBusiness communication. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a21st century.  aacademic.  aanthropology.  abusiness.  acommunication.  aconference call.  acorporate.  adigital workplace.  adigital world.  aeconomy.  aenglish language.  afinance.  afluency.  aglobal communication.  aglobal languages.  aglobal.  ainternational.  alanguage fluency.  alanguage learning.  alanguage.  amultinational.  aoral communication.  aresearch.  ascholarly.  aspeaking english.  atechnology.  aword choice.  aworking online.  aworldwide.1 aJarvenpaa, Sirkka L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052029137940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096517140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965171423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520965171/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a